@baseUrl = http://localhost:7071
# @baseUrl = https://<YOUR-FUNC>.azurewebsites.net

### A1) Auth Register (create user) - Expect: 201 Created
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "pingchili",
  "password": "P@ssw0rd123",
  "email": "pingchili@edu.sait.ca",
  "company": "F12.net",
  "telephone": "1234567890",
  "role": "Admin"
}

### A2) Auth Register duplicate - Expect: 409 Conflict
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "pingchili",
  "password": "P@ssw0rd123",
  "email": "pingchili@edu.sait.ca",
  "company": "F12.net",
  "telephone": "1234567890",
  "role": "Admin"
}

### A3) Auth Login (correct password) - Expect: 200 OK + authenticated=true
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "pingchili",
  "password": "P@ssw0rd123"
}

### A4) Auth Login (wrong password) - Expect: 401 Unauthorized
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "pingchili",
  "password": "WrongPass111"
}

### A5) Auth Login (unknown user) - Expect: 401 Unauthorized
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "not-exist-user",
  "password": "P@ssw0rd123"
}

### A6) Auth Register (weak password) - Expect: 400 BadRequest
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "weakpassuser",
  "password": "123",
  "email": "weak@edu.sait.ca",
  "company": "F12.net"
}